  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'For the "Speech," "Tooltips," and "Items" settings, press the ''+'' button
    first to download the template file. Once done editing the file, press the ''...''
    button of the relevant setting to select the now edited file. Pressing the ''x''
    button will revert that setting back to normal.


    For the "Music" setting,
    you will need to provide a ".zip" file containing all required music (including
    the non-edited tracks if applicable) NOT in a folder within the zip. The file
    names are the same as in the original game for music and the music file extension
    is ".mp3." You must provide the following tracks: chow.mp3, escaped.mp3, lightsout.mp3,
    lockdown.mp3, rollcall.mp3, shower.mp3, work.mp3, workout.mp3, and freetime.mp3.
    Note: the zip file can be named anything, but the tracks within the zip must
    follow the aforementioned track names.'
